    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The current military posture and activity patterns suggest a high level of operational tempo, with multiple aircraft and vessels deployed in support of Operation Epic Fury. The US Navy&#39;s carrier strike groups, amphibious ready groups, and destroyers are actively engaged in the Pacific and Atlantic, while the US Air Force&#39;s transport and tanker aircraft are providing critical airlift and refueling support. The increased activity and deployments indicate a heightened state of readiness and a focus on supporting ongoing operations. However, the depletion of Tomahawk cruise missile stocks and the strain on the aerial refueling fleet are concerns that need to be addressed to maintain a sustainable operational pace. The overall assessment is that the US military is actively engaged in multiple theaters, with a focus on supporting Operation Epic Fury and maintaining a strong deterrent posture.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
